laboratory_examinations.findings: Most of the radionuclide accumulated in the normal biliary pathway; a small amount accumulated in the fistula.
Contrast material slowly proceeding to the hepatic region.
Abnormal bronchial bifurcation originating in the right main bronchus; small amount of air and contrast material remaining in the liver seen in the follow-up scan.
Yellow, serous secretions from an anomalous orifice in the medial side of the right intermediate bronchus.
